summary: So this (bottom photo) is one of my “Master Artist” studies as declared as an assignment back in the 90s (early college).  Mr....
caption:
So this (bottom photo) is one of my “Master Artist” studies as declared as an assignment back in the 90s (early college).  Mr. Robert Hawkes was the professor. Taught me how to free my mind.  The work was done with graphite sticks on Canson paper (grey). 

In any case, the top photo, as you can tell, is Michelangelo’s Fury (Damned Soul).  The bottom one, again, is the study.  Obviously some proportion issues - but then again, this is a throwback of my own history with art.  

It’s interesting to look back and almost remember what you’ve done, how you did it, what’s changed and what you can reach back and take from it creatively.  A certain…spirit seems to stir again.  That’s just me probably…
